          <physDesc>
             <p>The colophon in BN-INDIEN 186β is one of the few instances where the statement concerning the end of copying precedes the date. (2) The scribe seems to have a peculiar handwriting. See in particular the ratio between the first and the second half of the glyph for ya ( [1r6]), and the head of va ( [1r8]).
                  </p>
